File: Tom Brady of the New England Patriots warms up prior to Super Bowl LIII against the Los Angeles Rams at Mercedes-Benz Stadium on February 03, 2019 in Atlanta, Georgia. JOHANNESBURG - New England Patriots quarterback and six-time Super Bowl winner Tom Brady is behind South Africa during this year's Rugby World Cup in Japan. WATCH: Konnichiwa Springboks! How to support the Boks in Japanese Brady posted a video on Friday, sending his support to the Boks who open their Rugby World Cup campaign against New Zealand's All Blacks on Saturday. Brady is regarded as the G.O.A.T (Greatest of All Time) by many NFL (National Football League) fans and experts. The Springboks will be hoping to make a big statement during this World Cup. A win over the mighty All Blacks would not be a bad way to start. The Boks are two-time Rugby World Cup champions, having lifted the trophy both in 1995 and 2007.